title.en: Key to Chrysis species of the Nordic and Baltic countries
Posterior margin of T3 medially pointed or rounded without teeth
Posterior margin of T3 with distinct teeth or angular prominences
Posterior margin of T3 almost evenly rounded, medially not pointed
Posterior margin of T3 medially somewhat pointed
Mesoscutum medially dark blue or blackish and laterally green or blue with golden reflections
Mesoscutum completely red or golden greenish, medially not darker than laterally
Scapal basin largely smooth (female) or finely punctured (male) without fine cross-ridging
Scapal basin medially with fine cross-ridging in both sexes
Medial teeth on the posterior margin of T3
Medial teeth on the posterior margin of T3 extending distinctly further posteriorly than lateral teeth, and usually located in close proximity
Medial teeth on the posterior margin of T3 not extending distinctly further posteriorly than lateral teeth, and/or not located in close proximity
Mesoscutum golden red or golden green.
Second metatarsomere at least 3.5 times as long as broad
Second metatarsomere at most 2.5 times as long as broad
Malar space shorter, at most 0.75 times basal width of mandible
Malar space longer, in profile equal to basal width of mandible
Black spots of S2 strongly oblique posteriorly in female
Black spots of S2 not strongly oblique posteriorly in female
Posterior margin of T3 with six teeth
Posterior margin of T3 with four teeth, these sometimes only shallow projections
Metasoma multicoloured, T1 and T2 dark blue or black with golden green or golden red bands posteriorly.
Black spots of S2 fused and short, not or only slightly extending to lateral margins of sternite
Black spots of S2 fused and broad, widely extending to the lateral margins of the sternite
Ovipositor relatively broad and strongly chitinised
T5 of female with transverse striae and longitudinal medial groove
T5 of female without transverse striae and medial groove
Head only slightly wider than high
Male genitalia with broad notch between parameres, gonostyle very short and cuspis apically curved
Male genitalia with narrow notch between parameres, gonostyle apically elongated (as long as cuspis) and cuspis apically straight
Propodeal tooth slightly convex or straight ventrally
Metasoma completely blue or blue-green, without red colour
Metasoma not completely blue or blue-green, always with red or golden colour
Mesoscutum medially not darker than laterally.
Mesoscutum distinctly darker medially than laterally
Black spots of S2 large and long, almost extending to middle of sternite.
Black spots of S2 smaller, distinctly separated in the middle.
T3 of female with distinct transverse bulge anterior to pit row.
T3 of female without transverse bulge anterior to pit row.
Male with short triangular apical teeth separated by wide intervals
Male with spiniform apical teeth separated by narrow intervals
T1 blue, T2 entirely golden red (female) or with large dark blue dorsal spot (male)
Both T1 and T2 golden red or reddish
T3 completely green, blue or violet, in contrast with colour of T1 and T2
T3 golden red or reddish, at most with blue or violet apical rim
Setae medially on metatibia longer than width of tibia
Setae medially on metatibia shorter than width of tibia
Mesoscutum medially green or blue in male
T2 without or with very weak longitudinal keel medially, posteriorly without lifted margin
T2 with a distinct smooth longitudinal keel medially, posteriorly with slightly raised margin
Punctation of T2 relatively fine and sparse, interstices as large as or larger than puncture diameter
Punctation of T2 relatively coarse and dense, interstices smaller than puncture diameter
Head in frontal view as wide as high
Head in frontal view slightly wider than high
Black spots of S2 three quarters length of sternite
Black spots of S2 half of length of sternite
Apical rim of T3 blue or violet, remaining tergite red
Apical rim of T3 golden red, of same colour as remaining tergite
Spurs of metatibia approximately equal in length
Spurs of metatibia distinctly unequal in length
Female metatarsus shorter than metatibia, second tarsomere twice as long as broad in lateral view
Female metatarsus longer than metatibia, second tarsomere at least three times longer than broad in lateral view
Mandible thicker (in male, medial width of mandible about two thirds of its basal width; in female, medial width of mandible more than half of its basal width), with or without subapical tooth
Mandible thinner (in male, medial width of mandible less than two thirds of its basal width; in female, medial width of mandible not more than half of its basal width), always without subapical tooth
Flagellomeres not distinctly nodular in female
Female mesoscutum laterally with scattered punctation
Female mesoscutum laterally with dense punctation
Pronotum short, length less than one fourth of its width
Pronotum longer, length at least one fourth of its width
Malar space long, approximately as long as broad in female, and somewhat shorter in male.
Malar space short, shorter than broad in both female and male
F1 of antenna without metallic sheen
F1 with metallic sheen (often very weak)
Frons with dense adpressed white pubescence
Frons usually with sparser and more erect pubescence
Punctation of tergites very fine and dense throughout, punctures of uniform size, surface dull
Punctation of tergites coarser and sparser, punctures of variable size, surface shiny
Sternites and legs ventrally coppery red
Sternites and legs ventrally always greenish
Frontal carina with four tooth-like tubercles medially
Frontal carina without four tooth-like tubercles
Head and mesosoma dorsally with white pubescence
Apical teeth of T3 relatively long and sharp
Pronotum blue or violet framed by lighter colour, mesoscutellum medially darker than laterally
T1 anteriorly and laterally blue-green or green, dorsally golden red
T1 laterally golden red or only slightly greenish, dorsally golden red
Shape of metasoma broad and compact
Shape of apical rim and apical teeth
Apical rim short and intervals between apical teeth shallow
Shape of apical rim and apical teeth variable
Posterior margin of S4 opaque and angled
Posterior margin of S4 semitransparent and almost straight
T3 dorsally straight or concave in lateral view
T3 dorsally convex in lateral view
T2 and T3 laterally completely dull, with dense coriaceous microsculpture between punctures
T2 and T3 laterally with shiny surface between punctures
Body shape and breadth of ovipositor
Elongate and usually large species, ovipositor thin
Body shape and breadth of ovipositor variable
S2 red with long black spots
Mandible extremely thin (in lateral view, medially as broad as apical segment of labial palp), dorsally smooth and impunctate
Mandible thicker (in lateral view, medially broader than apical segment of labial palp), dorsally always punctate.
Body slender and elongate, metasoma with almost parallel sides
S2 greenish with short, rounded black spots
Mesoscutum laterally with wide, strongly shining interstices between punctures
Body slender and elongate, metasoma with almost parallel sides
Body not as slender and elongate
Punctation of T2 anteriorly finer than on T1, posteriorly very sparse
T3 long, deeply depressed medially and strongly shining
T3 shorter, more shallowly depressed medially and not as strongly shining.
Apical teeth short and blunt, with a wide and shallow central interval
Apical teeth longer and/or sharper, shape of central interval variable
S2 with rectangular black spots and golden red colour
Black spots of S2 not as distinctly rectangular, colouration variable
Ovipositor broad (T5 broader than long), often only its apex exerted
S2 blue-green with relatively short and rounded black spots
Mandible thick (in lateral view, medial width of mandible about half of its basal width)
Apical rim of T3 long and central interval between apical teeth often angular.
Apical rim usually shorter and central interval more widely arcuate
Metasoma broader, with slightly convex sides
Metasoma more elongate, with more parallel sides
Punctation of T2 anteriorly sparser and finer, with shining interstices
Punctation of T2 anteriorly denser and coarser, without shining interstices
T3 with slightly sparser punctation, its surface thereby shinier
T3 with dense punctation, its surface dull
Head narrower, in frontal view only slightly broader than high
Head broader, in frontal view distinctly broader than high
Colour of mesosoma lighter and more greenish
Colour of mesosoma darker and more bluish
Hosts cavity-nesting species of Ancistrocerus and Euodynerus
Metasoma elongate with almost parallel sides
S2 with long and narrow black spots
Mandible thicker (medial width of mandible about half of its basal width)
Mandible thinner (medial width of mandible less than half of its basal width)
T2 anteriorly with dense, deep and coarse punctation, punctures becoming much sparser and finer posteriorly
T2 anteriorly with somewhat sparser and finer punctation, punctures becoming slightly sparser and finer posteriorly
T3 shiny or with weak microsculpture
Apical teeth of T3 sharply produced and apical rim with almost parallel lateral margins
Apical teeth of T3 not as sharply produced and apical rim with more angled lateral margins
Punctation of T2 and T3 coarse throughout
Punctation of T2 and T3 finer
Pubescence of vertex whitish or brownish
S2 green or blue with rectangular black spots
Mesoscutum shiny blue or greenish, punctures of same colour as interstices
Mandible very thin (medial width of mandible not more than one third of its basal width), basally strongly narrowing in lateral view
Mandible thicker (medial width of mandible more than one third of its basal width), gradually narrowing towards the apex
Scapal basin with sparse and well defined punctation
Scapal basin with denser and more coriaceous punctation
Vertex with brown or whitish pubescence
T3 relatively dull with distinct microsculpture between punctures
Mesoscutum dark blue to almost black
Metasoma usually broader and more compact
Mesoscutum laterally with green or blue punctures and black interstices
Mesoscutum entirely blue, violet or black, punctures and interstices generally of same colour
F1 1.3–1.5 times as long as F2
F1 1.5–1.7 times as long as F2
S2 posteriorly usually red with relatively rounded black spots
S2 dark green or blue with almost rectangular black spots
Pubescence of vertex whitish or light brown
Mandible thin (medial width of mandible about one third of its basal width), dorsally smooth, without or with only barely visible punctures.
Mandible thicker (medial width of mandible more than one third of its basal width), its dorsal surface always with small punctures
Body small and slender, metasoma elongate with almost parallel sides (habitus similar to Chrysis angustula)
S2 greenish with short rounded black spots
Posterior margin of propodeal tooth virtually straight and perpendicular to body axis
Posterior margin of propodeal tooth straight, convex or concave
Colour of S2 golden or reddish, with long rectangular black spots
Colour of S2 variable, black spots usually not rectangular
Body slender, metasoma with approximately parallel sides (habitus similar to Chrysis leptomandibularis)
Body usually more robust, metasoma with more convex sides
Punctation of T2 anteriorly usually finer than on T1, becoming sparser posteriorly, surface thereby strongly shining
Punctation of T2 anteriorly slightly finer or as coarse as on T1, surface posteriorly not as shining
T3 shiny, transition of lateral margin into lateral apical teeth straight, apical rim and teeth short
T3 shiny or dull, transition of lateral margin into lateral apical teeth straight or concave, apical rim and teeth longer
Punctation of T2 anteriorly usually finer than on T1
Punctation of T2 anteriorly usually not finer than on T1
T3 with very fine and regular punctation
T3 with coarser and/or more irregular punctation
S2 usually greenish with relatively short black spots
S2 green, golden or red with often larger black spots
Mandible relatively thick (in lateral view, medial width of mandible more than half of its basal width)
Metasoma with slightly convex sides (approximately as in figure)
Metasoma with more parallel sides (approximately as in figure)
Head narrower, in frontal view only slightly broader than high
Head narrower, in frontal view distinctly broader than high
Colour of mesosoma predominantly lighter, often greenish
Colour of mesosoma predominantly darker, violet, blue or blue-green
Hosts cavity-nesting species of Ancistrocerus and Euodynerus
Mandible thick (medial width of mandible more than half of its basal width), its margins basally straight in lateral view
Mandible thinner (medial width of mandible not more than half of its basal width), its margins basally more or less concave in lateral view
T3 relatively shiny, transgression of lateral margin into lateral apical teeth straight or slightly concave
T3 relatively dull, transgression of lateral margin into lateral apical teeth slightly or strongly concave
F1 longer than or as long as F2
S2 mainly green, its pubescence dense and long
S2 mainly red or golden, its pubescence variable
F1 distally without or with a very shallow, inconspicuous impression
F1 distally with a shallow impression
Propodeal tooth usually laterally straight or convex
Pronotum without sharply contrasting border between the darker middle part and the lighter margins
Pronotum usually with sharply contrasting border between the darker middle part and the lighter margins
Punctation of T2 anteriorly coarse or relatively fine
Transgression of lateral margin of T3 into lateral apical teeth
Transgression of lateral margin of T3 into lateral apical teeth straight
Transgression of lateral margin of T3 into lateral apical teeth slightly concave
Central interval of apical teeth more angulate, and pits of apical rim smaller
Central interval of apical teeth more arcuate, and pits of apical rim larger
F1 approximately as long as or slightly (not more than 1.2×) longer than F2
F1 1.2–1.5 times as long as F2
T2 more finely punctured, punctures becoming slightly sparser posteriorly
Punctation of T3 coarse and dense
Apical teeth of T3 long and sharp
Apical teeth of T3 not as sharp
Black spots of S2 relatively large and rectangular
Black spots of S2 not as rectangular
Mandible thinner, its margins basally concave in lateral view
Mandible thicker, its margins basally almost straight in lateral view
F1 1.2–1.4 times as long as F3
F1 1.2–1.5 times as long as F2
Sternites usually golden green or golden red
Size of black spots of S2
Size of black spots of S2 variable
F1 1.2–1.4 times as long as F2
F1 1.3–1.5 times as long as F2
Size of black spots of S2
Size of black spots of S2 variable
Punctation of mesoscutum coarser, punctures often with lighter colour compared to interstices
Punctation of mesoscutum finer, punctures not differing in colour from interstices
